The "blended wing body" is a revolutionary airframe design that transforms an aircraft into essentially a flying wing, resembling the military's stealth aircraft in appearance.
The extension of the cabin into the wing allows the drag associated with the traditional aircraft body to be reduced, and permits some weight reduction, as well.
With this radical new design, fuel burn could be "reduced significantly relative to that of conventionally designed transports" (Lewis and Niedzwiecki, 1999, p. 7-13).
