The Federal government, primarily the DOE, currently spends several hundred million dollars annually in support of the development of advanced vehicle technology, including fuel cells, hybrid drivetrains, advanced diesel power plants, advanced materials, and so forth.
Other agencies, e.g., Department of Transportation (DOT), National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), Department of Defense (DoD), and so forth, sponsor additional research in other transportation areas.
